{
  "texts": [
    "So far, the literature on affective artifacts has largely focused on ordinary and relatively low-tech objects (cf.",
    "above; see also Piredda 2020, Colombetti and Roberts 2015, and Colombetti and Krueger 2015 for further examples).",
    "On the one hand, this tendency seems reasonable.",
    "First of all, many of these objects play paradigmatic emotivity-regulating roles, being highly personalized and easily felt as part of one's self.",
    "Moreover, these objects are typically quite ordinary ones, possessed and regularly used by many people."
  ]
}